Tiger Softball Fans Sept. 11 & 12, 2020

Tickets will be available through "Go fan"

Here is the link for the ticket purchase for the tournament.
https://gofan.co/app/school/CO71945_1

On Friday Sept 11 gates will open at 1:00pm,
on Saturday Sept 12 gates will open at 8:00am.
All players, parents and coaches will be required to have temp checks as well as wear a mask in the facility.

It will be on GoFan but under Runyon Field Sports Complex. GoFan is working on the site and should have it completed today with the ticket information loaded. If your fans cannot or do not have the capability of purchasing these tickets at home, they will be able to do so at the gate. We have an ipad available for fans to complete their purchase. We will also have a poster with a QSR Code that will take them directly to the correct site to purchase their tickets. We will take cash for the exact amount only. Tickets are $6 adults, $4 for students/seniors. That ticket will be good for one entire day. Saturday they will have to purchase an additional ticket.

La Junta Primary School
August 31 at 8:53 PM 路

We will be doing virtual PTO (Parent Teacher Organization) and PIE (Partners in Education) meetings this year!!!

Research shows that parent-school-partnerships improve schools, strengthen families, build community support, and increase student achievement and success. Both PTO and PIE committees are made up of staff members and parents/guardians but are completely parent/guardian led.

If you are a Primary School parent/guardian and are interested in joining, please click the link below to learn what each committee is and how you can get involved!

Once we have gathered information for all who are interested, we will send zoom meeting invites to your email address in order for you to be able to join the meetings. We look forward to seeing you at the first meetings soon!

Survey link:
https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeuYhif2SlmV1uCjIQzb-NESW2HvQnqrQEjdDE1uAPnx2-O_g/viewform?usp=sf_link

For all homebound online only kids: Meal pick up will be Mon-Thur from 11-11:30 am at the Tiger Trade Academy. A food service worker will be out front for convenient curb side pick-up of meals. Students do not need to be present for pick-up. Parents or students picking up meals will need to provide the following information: name, grade level, and if know it their student id. Meals will consist of that days lunch, snack, and the following days breakfast.

For all hybrid students 6-12 student will be receiving a bag with that days snack and the following days breakfast, lunch, and snack at the conclusion of their last period.

post_text:
La Junta Intermediate School

Monday, August 24th is the first day of school! We are very excited to start the year!
Students may get dropped off after 7:30am. Breakfast and classes begin promptly at 8:00am.
Each grade level will enter and be dismissed from their own designated door.
3rd grade - north door by the playground
4th grade - northwest door by glass windows
6th grade - southwest door by the glass windows entering the lunchroom
5th grade - south door by the basketball courts/carport
If your child is doing online learning, please check their school email for a message from their teacher. Have them join their class before 8:00am so they are ready for attendance and further instructions.
Update: Masks will be required for 5th and 6th grade students. 3rd and 4th grade students may wear masks if they would like but are not required. LJIS students will be allowed to bring backpacks.

Attention Parents and Students: We are attaching a welcome back with which door your student is to enter and a map showing the door numbers. You should have received a message from La Junta Jr/Sr High School letting you know that student learning groups have been assigned (Orange or Black).

ORANGE learning group:
In person at school on Mondays and Wednesdays
Attending school virtually Tuesday and Thursdays.

BLACK learning group:
In person at school on Tuesdays and Thursdays
Attending school virtually on Mondays and Wednesdays.

To find your student's learning group assignment in the message center of your campus parent or student portal. Click on the message center tab and then find the inbox. The information can also be seen under your student's account in the Calendar tab. Click on Calendar, then Schedule, and then click on a school day. It will then tell you if the student should be virtual that day or not.

Transportation

Junior/Senior High and Tiger Trades: Will be located in the Ag classroom at the High School.
Tuesday August 11th 11-6pm

Primary:
Wednesday August 12th 8am-12pm

Intermediate:
Wednesday August 12th 12pm-4pm

We will be requiring masks, temp checks at the door and only allowing 4 people in at a time, so since we are in a classroom we ask that only one parent come in to obtain bus passes and if possible leave children with another responsible adult. We will have our doors open for proper ventilation. We also still have our bus contract online (district website) for those who are available to print and complete them prior to coming, it should make things go quicker.

Any questions please just give me a call, thank you so much!!

post_text: East Otero R-1 is a CEP district and as such all students in our district qualify for the Pandemic-EBT, or P-EBT, which can help you feed your family while schools are closed. You will receive a card with approximately $279 per eligible child that you can use to purchase food at stores that accept EBT. If you already receive SNAP benefits and are eligible for P-EBT, these funds will automatically load into your existing account. If you do not currently receive SNAP benefits, apply here for P-EBT (application will open soon): https://www.colorado.gov/cdhs/p-ebt. You will need your child's SASID number which was text, emailed and is on the Inbox of your Campus Parent portal. If you need help accessing this information, please call Dee Rangel at 719-384-6906.

post_text:
Information for this weekend:

Cord Colors for cumulative GPA as of the end of the 1st Semester:

Gold - 4.0+ - Summa Cum Laude

Silver - 3.8-3.9 Magna Cum Laude

While - 3.4-3.7 Cum Laude

Mr. & Miss La Junta High

Criteria for Mr. & Miss La Junta High include:
-4 years at LJHS
-Minimum 2.0 GPA
-Enrolled in 3 classes senior year
(does not include TLC or Online; OJC classes count if receiving credit at LJHS)
-Citizenship
-School Service
-Participation in Activities and Academics

Athlete of the Year

Recipients: One senior male athlete
One senior female athlete

Criteria for nomination:
1. Nominee must be a two-sport varsity letter winner
2. Must have attended LJHS for four or more semesters
3. Athletic achievement
4. Academic achievement
5. Citizenship in school and community
6. Coachability
7. Leadership
Must have participated in at least two sports their senior year, unless prevented by circumstances beyond their control.

Mr. & Miss La Junta High - Congratulations to each of our Candidates:

Miss La Junta High: Sydney Copley, Bianca Good, Allyson Haugen, Hayden Mayo and Sara Noll.

Mr. La Junta High: Kody DiRezza, Orlando Estrada, Wyatt Hoeppner, Chance Oquist and James Reeder

Criteria for Mrs. & Miss La Junta High include:
4 years at LJHS
2.0 GPA
Enrolled in 3 classes senior year (does not include TTA or Online; OJC classes count if receiving credit at LJHS)
Citizenship
School Service
Participation in Activities and Academics

The top 5 candidates in each category were voted on by La Junta Jr/Sr High Staff. The winners of Mr. & Miss LJHS will be voted on by their peers in grades 9-12.

Mindset: Live to Give
Learning Objective: Make a Difference
Thought:
In a world that seems upside down, we need to take care of ourselves and the people around us. Grab a piece of paper and write your name, the name of someone you know, and a strangers name. During the upcoming week, do something kind for each person on the list. Random acts of kindness have been linked to many health benefits such as a reduction in anxiety, depression, and blood pressure.
Lets turn the world around with a few acts of kindness!

post_text:
AV-CTC Youth Recognition Awards

This seemed like an excellent time of year to focus our attention on some positives and celebrate all of the good things young people do locally.



The link to the first annual AV-CTC Youth Recognition Awards is below. These categories were created BY young people FOR young people. These awards are the community's opportunity to recognize our young people for the ways they are making the world better through kindness, laughter, creativity and so much more.

If you know a young person, aged 9 to 25 years old, please take a moment to nominate them in one of the categories below. Our Youth Involvement workgroup will do a blind review of all submissions and choose a winner in each category! All winners will receive a $50 gift card, certificate of appreciation and goodie bag!

Requirements:
Nominees must live in Bent, Otero, or Crowley Counties
Nominees must be ages 9 to 25

Submission deadline is May 22nd.

Nominate below and SHARE, SHARE, SHARE!

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeW23dJ3s8ZeE-u02vsDmyvGyqKeDD8eCEICp0SEfHYNpjAig/viewform

How to Feel Better in Difficult Times - 100% Accountable
shared_text:
7 Mindsets was live.
April 15 at 2:59 PM 路

How to Feel Better in Difficult Times - 100% Accountable

Jeff Waller, co-founder and co-author of 7 Mindsets kicks off his third weekly #adultSEL series by sharing 3 ways to stay accountable.

1. Find anything that makes you feel present, engages you or makes you feel mindful.

2. Practice gratitude. Write down 3 things you are grateful for every night before you go to sleep or think about something good that came out of a bad situation.

3. Seek ways to serve and help others.

Here is the YouTube link to share with your fellow educators and parents:

https://bit.ly/2xz5jkJ
.
.
.
#7Mindsets #SEL #socialemotionallearning #passionfirst #wholeteacherwholechild

TUNE IN EVERY WEDNESDAY - 11 am EST (Facebook LIVE series)

La Junta Jr/Sr High School STAR Leadership Class
STAR Leadership Class

Two informational Zoom (online) meetings have been scheduled for our new course offering, STAR Leadership with Mr. Schmidt:
- Monday, April 20th @ 3:30 pm
- Friday, April 24th @ 5:30 pm

The Junior Reserve Officers Training Corps (JROTC) is one of the largest character development and citizenship programs for youth in the world - instilling in students the values of citizenship, service to the United States, and personal responsibility and a sense of accomplishment. JROTCs mission: "To Motivate Young People to be Better Citizens", is the guide post for the programs success.

If you would like to attend an informational meeting about our STAR Leadership Class, please provide your contact information by completing the form below and submit it before Sunday, April 19th at 7:30 pm. You will receive an email with the Zoom (online) meeting link for the day you have chosen to attend. Please check your email.
https://forms.gle/NAT1ama9CT8J58A36

post_text:
To the La Junta Community,
In an attempt to limit exposure of staff, volunteers, parents, and children to COVID-19, food service will be shifting from a daily distribution schedule to a twice weekly distribution schedule. Beginning Monday, April 13, 2020, meals will be distributed at all sites on Mondays and Thursdays. You will receive Monday through Wednesday's meals on Monday, and Thursday through Sunday's meals on Thursday. We will continue to offer these meals in a drive-up, take and go style at all of the current locations (Primary School, Intermediate School, and Tiger Trades Academy-East School) from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. We appreciate all of your support and cooperation as we continue to navigate these trying times.
Thank you,
East Otero Food Service

post_text: Rena Henegar is attending Honor Choir at Western State. They had auditions at the end of October. Dr. Roberson (choir chair at the school) said that last year they generally have 400 or so auditions from around the state of Colorado. It is such an honor to make the groups. There will be a concert Saturday afternoon at 2:00. The Gunnison firefighters help with the event as well and it is a community fundraiser/outreach.

LJIS is launching the Original Works art fundraiser this week! Students who had art class today took their packets home  Remaining packets for all other students in art class will go home tomorrow.

Original Works will print your child's artwork on various products such as mugs, mouse pads, aprons, and so on. They make great keepsakes and gifts for all! The items are set to arrive at the end of April.

The deadline to order is next Thursday, March 12th. Only checks and money orders will be accepted as a form of payment. Please contact Mrs. Pacheco if you have any questions.
